fields.content:
The vicious Downing Street civil war escalated again today as insiders voiced fury at 'vicious and cowardly' attacks on Carrie Symonds - including jibes that she wants to be the 'new Princess Diana'. 

The wave of negative briefing is threatening to tear the government apart, with complaints from the Vote Leave faction that the PM's fiancee is trying to 'run the government by WhatsApp' from the No11 flat. 

It has emerged that allies of Dominic Cummings and former director of communications Lee Cain have been referring to Ms Symonds as 'Princess Nut Nut' for months.
fields.title: Fury at 'vicious and cowardly' attacks on Carrie Symonds amid claims Cummings allies branded her 'Princess Nut Nut' and accused her of 'wanting to be the new Princess Diana'

fields.content:
Cheltenham behind closed doors might be a dispiriting experience, but Coole Cody produced a performance to lift a despondent heart with a gutsy win in the Paddy Power Gold Cup that acted as a reminder of the drama the home of jump racing can deliver.

A bare reading of the result with 10-1 shot Coole Cody's three-and-a-quarter-length win from Spiritofthegames does not get close to doing justice of the winner's performance, leading from the third fence, surviving an horrendous slip at the fourth and then maintaining a relentless gallop to see off what was an above-average line-up.

On only his fourth start for trainer Evan Williams, Coole Cody also delivered a significant and timely ninth winner of the season for jockey Tom O'Brien.
fields.title: Coole Cody produces red-hot performance to win Cheltenham's Paddy Power Gold Cup as jockey Tom O'Brien toasts ninth win of the season

fields.content:
She is preparing for the release of her debut album, Life Support, later this year. 

And Madison Beer made sure all the attention was on her on Friday evening as she headed to Catch restaurant with a friend in full Halloween garb. 

The singer, 21, put on a leggy display and showcased her washboard stomach in a vibrant nurse Halloween outfit as she sauntered through West Hollywood.
fields.title: Madison Beer flaunts her incredibly ripped abs and VERY perky cleavage in sizzling nurse costume as she twins with a pal for Halloween night out

fields.content:
She wowed the Strictly judges on Saturday night, when she and dance partner Aljaz Skorjanec's Charleston topped the leaderboard with an impressive 29 points.

And on Sunday morning Clara Amfo revealed just how much blood, sweat and tears must be invested to do well on the show, as she took to her Instagram story to show off a hand injury.  

The Radio 1 presenter, 36, showed her hand bandaged up in an orange plaster as she explained that she had hurt it 'at some point' during the previous night.
fields.title: 'Too much enthusiastic Charlstoning': Strictly's Clara Amfo reveals hand injury the day after topping the leaderboard with her 'perfect' Charleston

fields.content:
ZARA McDermott appeared to confirm she's back together with ex Sam Thompson after she was spotted sneaking out of his house at 9am.

The Made in Chelsea stars split in September after she cheated during X Factor: Celebrity last year.

Since then Zara has been on a mission to win back Sam after he broke up with her because of her infidelity.

Despite the furore, it appears that the duo are back on track after Zara was spotted making a hasty exit from Sam's house - before he later emerged.

And now the Love Island star was pictured in an oversized purple hoodie, which looked similar to one Sam wore to an event in April last year.

Sporting a face mask, Zara attempted to remain incognito with the hood pulled over her hair and draped a plaid shirt jacket over her arm.
fields.title: BACK ON Zara McDermott and Sam Thompson pictured back together after she cheated on him as she sneaks out of his house
